The paper deals with strategy synthesis in partially observable Markov decision processes (POMDPs) and proposes an abstraction refinement framework to turn POMDP models into probabilistic two-player games (PGs). This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Game Theory (cs.GT), and Systems and Control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper uses a running example of an agent moving inside an environment with randomly moving obstacles, which suggests that it may also belong to the categories of Robotics (cs.RO) and Programming Languages (cs.PL) as these categories often deal with similar scenarios.
